{"title":"Marcapasos_Transcutaneo_Emergencia_iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica/Marcapasos_Transcutaneo_Emergencia_iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"MARCAPASOS\\NTRANSCUTÁNEO EN\\NEMERGENCIAS","guid":"cEz56XtrV_UR1kqDQkv2yA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Definición y\\Nprincipio","guid":"AIqQnE9jr-RmHlU1MoXzZQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Impulsos eléctricos a través de parches transtorácicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Vencen impedancia de caja torácica → despolarización miocárdica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Despolarización eléctrica → contracción mecánica biventricular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Método PUENTE → NO definitivo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"NO INVASIVO → fácil de programar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Nivel de evidencia SIMILAR a marcapasos endovenoso temporal (ACLS 2020)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"0","text":"Indicaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"Bradicardia INESTABLE que NO responde a atropina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"Bradicardia donde atropina NO está indicada","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"BAV 2do grado Mobitz II (INFRAHISIANO)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"BAV 3er grado (COMPLETO) → especialmente QRS ancho","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"8","text":"Signos de INESTABILIDAD hemodinámica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"Hipotensión arterial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"Signos de falla cardíaca","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"13","text":"Signos de CHOQUE → llenado capilar >3 seg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"13","text":"Dolor torácico isquémico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"13","text":"Alteración del estado de alerta","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"8","text":"Puente a marcapasos endovenoso temporal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"8","text":"Puente a marcapasos definitivo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"8","text":"Puente a resolución de etiología (hipercalemia, SCA, etc.)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"0","text":"Colocación\\Nde parches","guid":"X58aPXltaEED1_JoVTUcvQ","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"Posición ANTEROAPICAL (estándar)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"Parche 1 → subclavicular derecho (esternón)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"Parche 2 → ápex cardíaco (zona apical izquierda)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"26","parent":"22","text":"Posición ANTEROPOSTERIOR (alternativa preferida)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"Parche 1 → ápex cardíaco (anterior)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"Parche 2 → posterior, bajo escápula derecha (zona libre ósea)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"26","text":"Ventaja → mejor transmisión impulso eléctrico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"26","text":"Ventaja → estabilidad en decúbito prolongado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"22","text":"Parches DIRIGIDOS hacia zona ventricular","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"0","text":"Programación →\\N2 PARÁMETROS","guid":"J6K1LRwsO0cx9QsrZRXn-A","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"1) FRECUENCIA CARDÍACA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"Inicio recomendado → 60-80 lpm","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"Algunos monitores inician en 70 lpm automático","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"33","text":">80 lpm → NO beneficio descrito","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"33","text":"Ajustar según respuesta hemodinámica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"32","text":"2) MILIAMPERIOS (mA) → energía de estimulación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"Inicio bajo → ir subiendo progresivamente (5-10 mA por paso)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"SUBIR hasta lograr CAPTURA ELÉCTRICA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"38","text":"Espiga del MCP seguida de QRS ancho = CAPTURA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"38","text":"Una vez captura → AUMENTAR 10% sobre nivel de captura","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"38","text":"Ejemplo → captura a 40 mA → fijar ~44-50 mA (margen seguridad)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"0","text":"Modos de\\Nestimulación","guid":"BDzjBT-WFPsR1m10Vak_nQ","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"SINCRÓNICO (a demanda) → PREFERIDO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"Estimula SOLO si no hay actividad intrínseca","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"45","text":"Detecta ritmo nativo → inhibe estímulo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"45","text":"Permite identificar recuperación del ritmo propio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"45","text":"MENOR riesgo de fenómeno R sobre T","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"50","parent":"44","text":"ASINCRÓNICO (fijo)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"Estimulación CONTINUA independiente de ritmo nativo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"Riesgo → fenómeno R sobre T → arritmias ventriculares","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"50","text":"Indicación → cuando sincrónico NO captura adecuadamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"50","text":"Ejemplo → BAV 3er grado donde ondas P inhiben modo demanda","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"44","text":"Muchos monitores SOLO tienen modo fijo → aceptable si es la única opción","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"0","text":"Captura\\NELÉCTRICA y\\NMECÁNICA","guid":"V1qYdXYxDK1oSjp_GlZZhg","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Captura eléctrica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"Espiga de MCP seguida de QRS ancho en monitor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"NECESARIA pero NO SUFICIENTE","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"60","parent":"56","text":"Captura MECÁNICA → OBLIGATORIO verificar","guid":"","children":[{"id":"61","parent":"60","text":"Pulso palpable (pulso duro/mecánico) en arteria radial u otra","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"60","text":"Mejoría de presión arterial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"60","text":"Mejoría de llenado capilar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"60","text":"Mejoría del estado de alerta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"60","text":"Mejoría de signos de falla cardíaca","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"60","text":"Remisión de dolor torácico isquémico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"56","text":"Si captura eléctrica SIN mejoría hemodinámica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Agregar VASOPRESOR → norepinefrina (efecto alfa + beta)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"Considerar INOTRÓPICO si hipocontractilidad (ej: SCA extenso)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"Evaluación ecocardiográfica (FOCUS) recomendada","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"71","parent":"0","text":"Sedoanalgesia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"INICIAR después de confirmar captura eléctrica Y mecánica → NO antes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"71","text":"Procedimiento DOLOROSO e INCÓMODO para el paciente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"71","text":"Analgesia → FENTANILO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"Dosis → 0.5-1 mcg/kg peso ideal (bolos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"74","text":"Puede subir 1-3 mcg/kg si no hay riesgo de IOT","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"77","parent":"71","text":"Sedación → MIDAZOLAM","guid":"","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"Dosis → 0.05-0.1 mg/kg peso ideal (bolos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"77","text":"Proporciona sedación ligera + amnesia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"71","text":"Bolos a DOSIS RESPUESTA → sin infusión continua (uso temporal)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"71","text":"PRECAUCIÓN → ambos bajan resistencias vasculares sistémicas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"71","text":"En choque cardiogénico → RVS están elevadas como compensación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"71","text":"Sedación excesiva → elimina compensación → EMPEORA perfusión","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"0","text":"Duración y\\Ntransición","guid":"Gq3_y1m2yxpRI8qqbdohhg","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"Duración recomendada → 1-2 HORAS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"MÁXIMO 24 horas (parches pierden adhesividad)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"84","text":">60-120 min → considerar MARCAPASOS TRANSVENOSO TEMPORAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"84","text":"A la par → MANEJAR ETIOLOGÍA de bradiarritmia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"Hipercalemia → corrección electrolítica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"SCA → reperfusión (ICP o fibrinólisis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"88","text":"Enfermedad degenerativa del nodo → MCP definitivo","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"0","text":"Función\\NPAUSA","guid":"F_GCXmiaCbwkzvczCD58Rw","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"Permite desenmascarar ritmo cardíaco basal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"Útil para tomar ECG de 12 derivaciones interpretable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"92","text":"Uso BREVE → caerá perfusión al pausar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"0","text":"Errores\\Nfrecuentes","guid":"ZAVhsTalQbZKinMPZI_yTQ","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"Captura eléctrica ≠ perfusión → VERIFICAR siempre captura mecánica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"Retrasar MCP esperando\\Nrespuesta farmacológica","guid":"BgjxmjCoyEUXFeWyZagL1w","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"Atropina ineficaz con 1 dosis (1 mg IV) → NO esperar 3 dosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"98","text":"15 min de espera → riesgo de PCR y falla orgánica progresiva","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"96","text":"Sedoanalgesia excesiva → colapso hemodinámico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"96","text":"Sedoanalgesia ANTES de confirmar captura → ERROR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"96","text":"Temor excesivo a incomodidad del paciente → retrasa el procedimiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"96","text":"Uso prolongado SIN plan de transición","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"96","text":"NO manejar etiología de la bradiarritmia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"106","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones\\NGERIÁTRICAS","guid":"KhYwhhrt2Bs63SiVUbjlsw","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"Mayor impedancia torácica → puede requerir mA más altos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"FRAGILIDAD → menor reserva hemodinámica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"106","text":"Sedoanalgesia → ajustar dosis a peso ideal, titular cuidadosamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"106","text":"BZD → mayor riesgo de delirium en AM → minimizar dosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"106","text":"Considerar DEXMEDETOMIDINA como alternativa si disponible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"106","text":"Polifarmacia → revisar fármacos bradicardizantes (BB, BCC, digoxina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"106","text":"Hipotiroidismo y alteraciones electrolíticas → causas reversibles frecuentes en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"106","text":"Proporcionalidad terapéutica → evaluar CFS y voluntades anticipadas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClínicas","guid":"LGhIu0ilOx8RADYFA8LhMA","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Atropina 1 mg IV sin respuesta = INEFICAZ → NO esperar 3 dosis, iniciar MCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"BAV Mobitz II y BAV completo → atropina puede EMPEORAR (bloqueo infrahisiano)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"115","text":"Posición anteroposterior → mejor para uso prolongado y mejor captura","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"115","text":"Captura eléctrica sin mecánica → agregar norepinefrina como coadyuvante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"115","text":"Función PAUSA → útil para ECG diagnóstico (SCA) sin retirar MCP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"115","text":"Modo sincrónico SIEMPRE preferido → cambiar a fijo solo si falla captura","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"115","text":"Fenómeno R sobre T en modo fijo → riesgo arritmias ventriculares","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"115","text":"En AM → BZD aumentan riesgo delirium, preferir mínima dosis o alternativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"115","text":"Siempre buscar y tratar la ETIOLOGÍA → MCP es solo PUENTE","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"125","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"→ Algoritmo Bradicardia ACLS (Emergencias)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"→ Bloqueos AV (Cardiología)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"125","text":"→ Sedoanalgesia UCI (Farmacología)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"125","text":"→ Delirium en UCI (Geriatría)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"125","text":"→ Choque Cardiogénico (Hemodinamia)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"131","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"1. Sherbino J, et al. Prehospital transcutaneous cardiac pacing for symptomatic bradycardia or bradyasystolic cardiac arrest: a systematic review. Resuscitation. 2006;70(2):193-200.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"131","text":"2. Armour R, et al. Paradoxical worsening of bradycardia following atropine administration. Br Paramed J. 2022;7(2):38-42.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"131","text":"3. Panchal AR, et al. 2020 AHA Guidelines for CPR and ECC: Adult Advanced Cardiovascular Life Support. Circulation. 2020;142(16 Suppl 2):S366-S468.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"131","text":"4. Kusumoto FM, et al. 2018 ACC/AHA/HRS Guideline on the Evaluation and Management of Patients with Bradycardia and Cardiac Conduction Delay. Circulation. 2019;140(8):e382-e482.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"131","text":"5. Ider Samarrón. Marcapasos transcutáneo en emergencia. Entrenamiento en Áreas Críticas [YouTube]. 2024.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":136,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"UCI/Medicina Crítica","folder":"Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica","filename":"Marcapasos_Transcutaneo_Emergencia_iPad","id":"map_2329","resolved_references":[]}